In general, the shunt resistance can be engineered to the extent that the resulting penalty on the efficiency is negligible. Therefore, in the following, we focus on evaluating the impact of series resistance and assume the shunt resistances are infinitely large for both LED and the PV cell. For GaN LEDs, a series resistance as small as 1mΩ⋅cm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
